node.text:
Yesterday’s home-cooked dinner. Fried rice with honey baked ham, shrimps and leeks - forgot that I have Bak Kwa (pork jerky) which would take the tastiness to the next level. Had it with Putien Restaurant’s Spice Mum Chili Sauce which has both sweet and sour notes that I like.
.
